The new documentation on [Connecting JIRA applications to PostgreSQL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver070/installing-jira-applications/connecting-jira-applications-to-a-database/connecting-jira-applications-to-postgresql] is missing some commands for the DB creation that were in the [old docs|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jira/connecting-jira-to-postgresql-185729433.html].
This missed commands cause JIRA to complain about the DB collation/encoding.

Old documentation:
{noformat}
CREATE DATABASE jiradb WITH ENCODING 'UNICODE' LC_COLLATE 'C' LC_CTYPE 'C' TEMPLATE template0;
or
$ createdb -E UNICODE -l C -T template0 jiradb
{noformat}
New documentation:
{noformat}
CREATE DATABASE jiradb WITH ENCODING 'UNICODE';
or 
$ createdb -E UNICODE jiradb
{noformat}

